  "text": "Smart mobile devices have become essential tools in many people's daily lives. Not only are we using these devices as the means to communicate with others, as sources of entertainment and as ways of expressing ourselves, but we also use them to store sensitive personal information and access different online services. Despite all the information contained in a device and the transactions that can be performed with it, many users choose not to protect their devices [CITATION_1] , and at the same time they tend to be perpetually logged into some of the services provided by mobile third party applications. Thus, an attack on the mobile device, or the loss of it, can have negative consequences, such as the intrusion of privacy, the opportunity to impersonate users, and even severe financial loss.",
